  Locus:
    Page: 415
    Verse: 2
Tags:
  - Selfishness
---
Selfish people are, by definition, those whose activities are devoted to
bringing themselves happiness. Yet ... these selfish people are far less
likely to be happy than those whose efforts are devoted to making others
happy.
